content: Warburton is a surname of English origin. It is derived from two Old English words "weard" meaning "guard" and "burh" meaning "fortress" or "town." The name originally referred to a person who lived or worked at a fortified town or a watchman who guarded the town. The surname Warburton is most commonly found in the county of Cheshire in North West England, and it has been borne by several notable people throughout history.
